          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3 mb-md-0">
          <div class="card py-4 h-100">
            <div class="card-body text-center">
              <i class="fas fa-mobile-alt text-primary mb-2"></i>
              <h4 class="text-uppercase m-0">Phone</h4>
              <hr class="my-4">
              <div class="small text-black-50">+1 (555) 902-8832</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="social d-flex justify-content-center">
        <a href="#" class="mx-2">
          <i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="bg-black small text-center text-white-50">
    <div class="container">
      Copyright &copy; Khorshed Dubash 2019
    </div>
  </footer>

  <!-- Plugin JavaScript -->
  <script src="https://blackrockdigital.github.io/startbootstrap-grayscale/vendor/jquery-easing/jquery.easing.min.js"></script>

  <!-- Custom scripts for this template -->
  <script src="https://blackrockdigital.github.io/startbootstrap-grayscale/js/grayscale.min.js"></script>

</body>

</html>

<div class='container'>
  <div class = 'row'>
      <p class = 'col-md-12'> 
          Magic: The Gathering is the world's first, and most successful <%= link_to "Tradeable Card Game", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collectible_card_game#Overview" %>. 
          Released in late 1993, it was an immediate success and cards sold out immediately, with the company,  <%= link_to "Wizards of the Coast", "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wizards_of_the_Coast" %> initially
          unable to meet demand for over a year. 
      </p>

  </div>

  <div class = 'row'>
      <p class = 'col-md-8'> 
          Of this 295-card set, some ended up being very highly sought-after-- a very few, in particular, and one above all else: Black Lotus.
      </p>

      <br> 
      <br> 

      <p class = 'col-md-7'>
        In the early days of Magic, an Alpha Black Lotus could be had for around $50; as late as 1999, they could be bought for around $400. Today, they rarely go for under $10,000, except in very poor condition,
        and regularly sell for many tens of thousands; Lotuses in mint condition have sold for well over $100,000.
      </p>

      <p class = 'col-md-7'>
        The second-most sought after cards are the original five Moxes (or "Moxen"; the Mox Emerald, Ruby, Sapphire, Jet and Pearl), Ancestral Recall, Timetwister, and Time Walk. Collectively, in addition to Black Lotus, they are known as the Power Nine.
      </p>
  </div>
</div>